<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call strcmp(method, "GET") can dereference beyond the bounds of the object referenced by method if method is NULL or not NUL-terminated. For example, if the caller passes method == NULL (or a pointer to a non-terminated buffer), strcmp will attempt to read through memory and cause undefined behaviour. Thus the use of strcmp here violates Rule 21.17 unless the code guarantees beforehand that 'method' is a valid, NUL-terminated string (which is not shown).
</scenario>
